Cut 15-inch x 15-inch square from heavy cardboard or thick foam core board for base. Cut walls and roof of house from Pepperidge Farm cookie boxes or heavy cardboard. Beat egg whites, cream of tartar and confectioners sugar in large bowl with electric mixer on high speed 5 minutes or until stiff peaks form. Spoon about 1 cup icing into pastry bag fitted with plain or star tip. Cover bowl with damp cloth to prevent remaining icing from drying out. Assemble house using icing as glue. Make sure to glue walls to base as well as to each other, holding each piece in place 5 minutes before moving on to next. Let stand 3 hours or until house is completely dry before decorating. Decorate house with Pepperidge Farm cookies, using icing as glue.